<h1>What is application.ini?</h1>
The <b>application.ini</b> file holds all of the configuration options for your application and all of its environments. This could be database credentials, api keys, or simply variables in your application that should be set differently for different environments. 
<br><br>

Here is an example application.ini file which holds settings for production and development environments:<br>
<xmp class='cli'>[production]
;======================================
; Database Settings
;======================================
resources.db.adapter = PDO_MYSQL
resources.db.isDefaultAdapter = true
resources.db.host = localhost
resources.db.username = dblogin
resources.db.password = GFG63GVg!f
resources.db.database = mydatabase

;======================================
; API Keys
;======================================
apis.mandrill.api_key = "SDFGDFHD7786876FSDDFGdsdf"
apis.facebook.api_key = "fff786s87uidsjkjkdjkhfjkd8988"

