<h2>Accessing Settings From application.ini</h2>
You can access the settings registered in application.ini from any controller in any module.
<br><br>
Here is an example of getting the facebook API key from above:<br>
<xmp class='cli'>$facebookAPIKey = $this->_config->apis->facebook->api_key; </xmp>
<br>
<h2>Accessing Settings Directly</h2>
Although Nectar will automatically deliver the settings to your controller, if you need to access them directly you can do so like this:
<xmp class='cli'>//get config
$config = new Config;
$application = $config->getConfig();
$facebookAPIKey =  $application->apis->facebook->api_key; </xmp>
